	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99263283248811><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99263283248811>LoH macro possible?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99263283248811#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52529><span id=Scholar>Ryanlynx</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 15th 3:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Many times I'm grouped with more than one paladin and when things get tight we all end up LoHing the same player. This is usually fixed by dividing the group between the number of pally's and "babysitting" them (I keep an eye on half the group and he/she watches the other half). This works fine, but I'd still like to make an "automatic warning" button.<br><br>/say "I will LoH to %T in 5 seconds"<br>then 5 seconds later the LoH heals the player<br><br>Is this possible?<br>&nbsp;<br>Ryanlynx<br>Paladin of Mith Marr<br>Xev<br><br>"Honor before Humility and all that jazz."</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
