<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=99288347439887></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99288347439887><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99288347439887>RE: LoH macro possible?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99288347439887#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=600><span id=Guru>PraetorFenix</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>277 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 18th 12:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.24]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Under your abilities menu, set the first button to Lay Hands.&nbsp;&nbsp;Have your hotkey do this:<br><br>/g LoH on %t in 5 seconds<br>/pause 50<br>/doability 1<br><br>The downside to this is, you can't do anything else while the hotkey is in effect.  It works well on raids though when one less melee for five seconds isn't as big a deal.<br><br>Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br><b>Praetor</b>, 60th Crusader<br>Avatars of Discord</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
