	   <a name=99263385448960></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99263385448960><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99263385448960>RE: skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=99263385448960#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20703><span id= >Torsk</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>208 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jun 15th 3:37 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Tailoring is more of a money maker for you , in your ealier levels, whereas smithing can be very costly. <br>With smithing, get your skill to 21, any way u can, skill points, making leather armour, etc.<br>when u get to lvl 21 , kill spiderlings, wholly spidres, etc, that drop spiderling silk. Combine 2 spiderling silk in sew kit to make silk thread.<br>when u kill wolves, bears, cats, make the ruined pelts into leather armour, for skill. Make all low quality, pelts into Leather padding & sell to blacksmiths , 100pp per stack. Convert all medium quality pelts into low quality , with the use of a skinning knife. sell High Quality Bear pelts for 25pp-30pp each to higher level tailors. I convert HQ cat & wolf pelts into low quality for Padding ( or Backing in older terminology)<br>I have found the 3 igloos in everfrost to be the very best place for harvesting both the silk & the pelts. Good Luck . This is an excellent phat plat maker.<br>Torsk Holynite, Ad Gloriam<br>Dwarf Paladin of the 40th Season<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>P.S. i did this at lvl 9-14 with my alt monk, made him a rich twink, hehe (earned enough plat to buy 2 fighting batons & Bamboo Bo at lvl 13!)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
