	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.83]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There is another way. It's boring, but won't take more than a few hours and costs less.&nbsp;&nbsp;That BIG orc you saw there by the Erudite...named Ortallius? He is a Paladin, believe it or not, and is factioned with the Temple of Ro. He hates Dervish Cutthroats.  You can kill the Cutthroats, get their Dervish rings and give them to Ortallius 3 at a time. No need to give 4, just 3. You can also buy them from lower level players in the zone. You will gain faction with the Temple of Ro for doing this. Obviously the Dervs are going to be VERY green to you at level 43, but wipe out the camp close by, repeat until you get rings, then give them to Ortallius. You can also con Ortallius to see how your faction is doing, before making the wasted run all the way to Lord Searfire. It's cheaper than the 30gp route. It just takes a little time.<br><br>Good luck fellow Dwarven Paladin!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>46th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
